<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Unit 1 | Observation, Bias & Memory</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #09111d;
      --panel: #111b2d;
      --panel-2: #18253d;
      --line: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
      --text: #eef4ff;
      --muted: #afbdd7;
      --accent: #32d4ff;
      --accent-2: #88f1ff;
      --gold: #ffd166;
      --green: #7ee3a8;
      --radius: 22px;
      --shadow: 0 18px 45px rgba(0,0,0,0.35);
    }

    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: Inter, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at top right, rgba(50,212,255,0.14), transparent 24%),
        radial-gradient(circle at left top, rgba(255,209,102,0.08), transparent 18%),
        linear-gradient(180deg, #07101c 0%, #0c1526 100%);
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    a { color: inherit; text-decoration: none; }
    .container { width: min(1200px, calc(100% - 2rem)); margin: 0 auto; }

    .topbar {
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      z-index: 50;
      backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
      background: rgba(7, 12, 22, 0.74);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    .nav {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 1rem;
      padding: 0.9rem 0;
    }

    .brand {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.8rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    }

    .brand-icon {
      width: 42px;
      height: 42px;
      border-radius: 14px;
      display: grid;
      place-items: center;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent), var(--gold));
      color: #07111b;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      font-size: 1.15rem;
    }

    .nav-links {
      display: flex;
      gap: 1rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .nav-links a {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 0.94rem;
    }

    .nav-links a:hover { color: var(--text); }

    .hero { padding: 4rem 0 2rem; }

    .hero-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.15fr 0.85fr;
      gap: 1.25rem;
      align-items: stretch;
    }

    .card {
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.03), rgba(255,255,255,0.015));
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    }

    .hero-card {
      padding: 2rem;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .hero-card::after {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      right: -40px;
      bottom: -40px;
      width: 220px;
      height: 220px;
      background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(50,212,255,0.18), transparent 65%);
      pointer-events: none;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.5rem;
      padding: 0.35rem 0.8rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: rgba(50,212,255,0.12);
      color: var(--accent-2);
      font-size: 0.84rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: 0.03em;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    h1, h2, h3 { line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 0.75rem; }
    h1 { font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 4rem); max-width: 12ch; }
    p { margin: 0; }

    .hero-copy {
      max-width: 60ch;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 1.04rem;
    }

    .hero-actions {
      display: flex;
      gap: 0.9rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
    }

    .btn {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      gap: 0.5rem;
      border-radius: 14px;
      padding: 0.9rem 1.2rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      transition: 0.2s ease;
    }

    .btn:hover { transform: translateY(-2px); }

    .btn-primary {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent), #7aeaff);
      color: #061018;
    }

    .btn-secondary {
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .side-card {
      padding: 1.2rem;
      display: grid;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .case-box,
    .stat-box,
    .mini-box {
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 18px;
      background: var(--panel-2);
    }

    .case-box { padding: 1rem; }
    .case-box h3 { margin-bottom: 0.35rem; }
    .case-box p { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.94rem; }

    .mini-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      gap: 0.8rem;
    }

    .mini-box {
      padding: 0.9rem;
      min-height: 100px;
    }

    .mini-box strong {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    }

    .mini-box span {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    .stats {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 0.8rem;
    }

    .stat-box {
      padding: 0.95rem;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .stat-box strong {
      display: block;
      font-size: 1.45rem;
      color: var(--gold);
    }

    section { padding: 1rem 0 2.4rem; }

    .section-head {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: end;
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
    }

    .section-head p,
    .muted { color: var(--muted); }

    .grid-3 {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .grid-2 {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 0.95fr 1.05fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .feature,
    .lesson,
    .info,
    .resource,
    .footer-card {
      padding: 1.25rem;
    }

    .feature-icon {
      width: 48px;
      height: 48px;
      border-radius: 14px;
      display: grid;
      place-items: center;
      background: rgba(50,212,255,0.12);
      margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
      font-size: 1.2rem;
    }

    .lesson {
      border-top: 4px solid var(--accent);
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.9rem;
    }

    .lesson-number {
      display: inline-block;
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      color: var(--accent-2);
      font-weight: 800;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    }

    .tags {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.45rem;
      margin-top: auto;
    }

    .tag {
      padding: 0.3rem 0.65rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .checklist,
    .resource-list,
    .assessment-list {
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.8rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .row {
      display: flex;
      gap: 0.8rem;
      align-items: flex-start;
      padding: 0.9rem 1rem;
      border-radius: 16px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    .row b { color: var(--text); }

    .resource-item {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 1rem;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 0.95rem 1rem;
      border-radius: 16px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    .resource-item small {
      display: block;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-top: 0.15rem;
    }

    .pill {
      white-space: nowrap;
      border-radius: 999px;
      padding: 0.35rem 0.72rem;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      font-weight: 800;
    }

    .pill.live { background: rgba(126,227,168,0.12); color: var(--green); }
    .pill.build { background: rgba(255,209,102,0.12); color: var(--gold); }

    .footer-card {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 1rem;
      align-items: center;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    @media (max-width: 1000px) {
      .hero-grid,
      .grid-2,
      .grid-3 { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
      .hero-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }

    @media (max-width: 700px) {
      .nav,
      .section-head,
      .footer-card { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
      .grid-2,
      .grid-3,
      .stats,
      .mini-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .hero-card,
      .feature,
      .lesson,
      .info,
      .resource,
      .footer-card { padding: 1.1rem; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="topbar">
    <div class="container nav">
      <a class="brand" href="../../index.html">
        <div class="brand-icon">🔬</div>
        <div>
          <div>Forensic Science</div>
          <small class="muted" style="font-weight:700;">Unit 1 Portal</small>
        </div>
      </a>
      <div class="nav-links">
        <a href="#overview">Overview</a>
        <a href="#lessons">Lessons</a>
        <a href="#resources">Resources</a>
        <a href="#assessment">Assessment</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <main>
    <section class="hero" id="overview">
      <div class="container hero-grid">
        <div class="card hero-card">
          <div class="eyebrow">👁️ Unit 1 • Observation, Bias & Memory</div>
          <h1>How reliable are your eyes and your memory?</h1>
          <p class="hero-copy">
            This opening unit trains students to think like investigators. Before analyzing fingerprints, blood, or DNA,
            students learn the most important lesson in forensic science: human perception is limited, memory is fragile,
            and careful documentation matters.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="#lessons">View Lessons</a>
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="#resources">Open Resources</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card side-card">
          <div class="case-box">
            <h3>Year-Long Case Launch</h3>
            <p>
              Students are introduced to the opening scene from the course mystery and immediately practice observation,
              inference, and evidence-based thinking.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="mini-grid">
            <div class="mini-box"><strong>Skill Focus</strong><span>Observation vs. inference, working memory, note-taking, scene sketching</span></div>
            <div class="mini-box"><strong>Big Idea</strong><span>Science helps overcome human error and unreliable perception</span></div>
            <div class="mini-box"><strong>Student Product</strong><span>Structured investigator notes, sketches, and evidence logs</span></div>
            <div class="mini-box"><strong>Instruction Style</strong><span>High-engagement labs, stations, image analysis, and mini cases</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="stats">
            <div class="stat-box"><strong>10</strong><span>Days</span></div>
            <div class="stat-box"><strong>6+</strong><span>Hands-On Activities</span></div>
            <div class="stat-box"><strong>1</strong><span>Mini Crime Scene</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head">
          <div>
            <h2>Unit Goals</h2>
            <p>Students begin by learning why careful observation and structured notes matter in every forensic investigation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid-3">
          <article class="card feature">
            <div class="feature-icon">🧠</div>
            <h3>Understand Human Error</h3>
            <p class="muted">Students explore selective attention, false memory, bias, and how quickly details can be lost or changed.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card feature">
            <div class="feature-icon">📝</div>
            <h3>Document Like an Investigator</h3>
            <p class="muted">Students practice structured note-taking, scene sketching, and separating observations from conclusions.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card feature">
            <div class="feature-icon">🔎</div>
            <h3>Launch the Case</h3>
            <p class="muted">Students use their first evidence packet to begin analyzing a mystery they will revisit throughout the course.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="lessons">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head">
          <div>
            <h2>Lesson Sequence</h2>
            <p>This structure gives the district a clear view of the academic direction of the course while keeping each lesson practical and engaging.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid-3">
          <article class="card lesson">
            <span class="lesson-number">Day 1</span>
            <h3>The Case Begins</h3>
            <p class="muted">Students receive the first case file and separate observations from inferences using a staged or photographed scene.</p>
            <div class="tags"><span class="tag">Case File</span><span class="tag">Observation</span></div>
          </article>
          <article class="card lesson">
            <span class="lesson-number">Day 2</span>
            <h3>Observation vs. Inference</h3>
            <p class="muted">Students practice identifying what is directly seen versus what is assumed.</p>
            <div class="tags"><span class="tag">Reasoning</span><span class="tag">Evidence</span></div>
          </article>
          <article class="card lesson">
            <span class="lesson-number">Day 3</span>
            <h3>Selective Attention</h3>
            <p class="muted">Students investigate how focused attention can cause important details to be missed.</p>
            <div class="tags"><span class="tag">Attention</span><span class="tag">Eyewitnesses</span></div>
          </article>
          <article class="card lesson">
            <span class="lesson-number">Day 4</span>
            <h3>Observation Stations Lab</h3>
            <p class="muted">Students rotate through fast-paced evidence stations and test how much detail they can accurately recall.</p>
            <div class="tags"><span class="tag">Stations</span><span class="tag">Recall</span></div>
          </article>
          <article class="card lesson">
            <span class="lesson-number">Day 5</span>
            <h3>Memory Reconstruction</h3>
            <p class="muted">Students experience how memories can shift when new information or suggestive questioning is introduced.</p>
            <div class="tags"><span class="tag">Memory</span><span class="tag">Bias</span></div>
          </article>
          <article class="card lesson">
            <span class="lesson-number">Day 6</span>
            <h3>Cognitive Bias</h3>
            <p class="muted">Students examine confirmation bias and expectation bias through simple forensic-style comparisons.</p>
            <div class="tags"><span class="tag">Bias</span><span class="tag">Claims</span></div>
          </article>
          <article class="card lesson">
            <span class="lesson-number">Day 7</span>
            <h3>Working Memory Skills</h3>
            <p class="muted">Students learn chunking, visual coding, and pattern recall strategies that strengthen short-term forensic recall.</p>
            <div class="tags"><span class="tag">Working Memory</span><span class="tag">Practice</span></div>
          </article>
          <article class="card lesson">
            <span class="lesson-number">Day 8</span>
            <h3>Forensic Notes</h3>
            <p class="muted">Students build their investigator notebook system and practice structured documentation from a sample scene.</p>
            <div class="tags"><span class="tag">Notebook</span><span class="tag">Documentation</span></div>
          </article>
          <article class="card lesson">
            <span class="lesson-number">Days 9–10</span>
            <h3>Scene Sketch & Mini Investigation</h3>
            <p class="muted">Students document a mini crime scene, produce a sketch, and defend their initial evidence-based conclusions.</p>
            <div class="tags"><span class="tag">Sketching</span><span class="tag">Mini Lab</span></div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="container grid-2">
        <article class="card info">
          <h2>Key Understandings</h2>
          <p class="muted">These ideas anchor the full course and make later forensic techniques feel purposeful instead of random.</p>
          <div class="checklist">
            <div class="row"><div>✅</div><div><b>Seeing is not the same as knowing.</b><br><span class="muted">Students learn that observation comes before interpretation.</span></div></div>
            <div class="row"><div>✅</div><div><b>Memory is reconstructive.</b><br><span class="muted">Eyewitnesses can be sincere and still be wrong.</span></div></div>
            <div class="row"><div>✅</div><div><b>Bias shapes conclusions.</b><br><span class="muted">Expectations can influence what people notice and how they interpret it.</span></div></div>
            <div class="row"><div>✅</div><div><b>Notes protect accuracy.</b><br><span class="muted">A careful record is more reliable than memory alone.</span></div></div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="card info" id="assessment">
          <h2>Assessment Snapshot</h2>
          <p class="muted">This unit ends with performance-based work instead of relying only on a traditional quiz.</p>
          <div class="assessment-list">
            <div class="row"><div>📓</div><div><b>Investigator Notebook Check</b><br><span class="muted">Students show organized observations, sketches, and documentation.</span></div></div>
            <div class="row"><div>🧪</div><div><b>Observation Stations Lab</b><br><span class="muted">Students demonstrate careful recording and evidence awareness.</span></div></div>
            <div class="row"><div>🖼️</div><div><b>Crime Scene Analysis</b><br><span class="muted">Students analyze a complex scene image using structured reasoning.</span></div></div>
            <div class="row"><div>🎯</div><div><b>Mini Crime Scene Investigation</b><br><span class="muted">Students observe, sketch, document, and defend a claim with evidence.</span></div></div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="resources">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head">
          <div>
            <h2>Unit 1 Resource Links</h2>
            <p>These link cards make the page look complete now and are ready to connect to live files as you build them.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid-3">
          <article class="card resource">
            <h3>Teacher Materials</h3>
            <div class="resource-list">
              <div class="resource-item"><div><strong>Unit Overview</strong><small>Goals, pacing, standards, and lesson flow</small></div><span class="pill live">Live</span></div>
              <div class="resource-item"><div><strong>Daily Plans</strong><small>Bell ringers, objectives, activities, and closure</small></div><span class="pill build">Building</span></div>
              <div class="resource-item"><div><strong>Answer Keys</strong><small>Keys for station labs and scene analysis</small></div><span class="pill build">Building</span></div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="card resource">
            <h3>Student Resources</h3>
            <div class="resource-list">
              <div class="resource-item"><div><strong>Case File 001</strong><small>Incident report, first scene image, and witness notes</small></div><span class="pill build">Building</span></div>
              <div class="resource-item"><div><strong>Observation Practice</strong><small>Warmups and image analysis tasks</small></div><span class="pill build">Building</span></div>
              <div class="resource-item"><div><strong>Notebook Pages</strong><small>Structured investigator note templates</small></div><span class="pill build">Building</span></div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="card resource">
            <h3>Lab Resources</h3>
            <div class="resource-list">
              <div class="resource-item"><div><strong>Observation Stations</strong><small>Station cards, response sheet, and setup guide</small></div><span class="pill build">Building</span></div>
              <div class="resource-item"><div><strong>Memory Lab</strong><small>False memory prompt and reflection sheet</small></div><span class="pill build">Building</span></div>
              <div class="resource-item"><div><strong>Mini Crime Scene</strong><small>Setup instructions and student evidence sheet</small></div><span class="pill build">Building</span></div>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="card footer-card">
          <div>
            <h2>Why this unit matters</h2>
            <p class="muted">When students understand how easily people miss, distort, or assume details, every later forensic method becomes more meaningful.</p>
          </div>
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="#overview">Back to Top</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
